4.Count uppercase and lowercase letters.
1st approach-->
s="AyuShI"
count_upper=0
count_lower=0
for ch in s:
    if 65<= ord(ch) <=90:
        count_upper+=1
    elif 97<= ord(ch) <=122:
        count_lower+=1
print(count_upper,count_lower)

#ord() is a built-in Python function that returns the Unicode code point
Time Complexity: O(n) (each character is checked once)
Space Complexity: O(1)



#2nd approach-->

s = "AyuShI"
upper = 0
lower = 0

for ch in s:
    if ch.isupper():
        upper += 1
    elif ch.islower():
        lower += 1

print(upper, lower)

Time Complexity: O(n) (each character is checked once)
Space Complexity: O(1)
